1.plot: In Trenton, Hawk races back to the tow lot to protect his wife and employees from an outraged car owner. Ponytail is attacked as evil incarnate for writing tickets in front of a Detroit hospital. And in Providence, Bonnie is confronted by a relentless man challenging the legitimacy of a parking sign.

2.title: Episode #6.2
2.plot: Mike and JoJo go head-to-head with irate residents as they tow cars from a Staten Island apartment complex. Eric's vigilance ticketing handicap parking violators in Detroit turns sour when angry citizens challenge his authority. In Providence, Maria's sweet demeanor is put to the test when a man accuses her of writing bogus tickets.

3.title: Episode #6.3
3.plot: The intrepid Johnny is called every name in the book by incensed illegal parkers in Providence. Uncle Jojo is confronted by angry Staten Island residents as he tows cars without residential permits. Sonjia tries to educate Detroit citizens about their parking violations but some blame her for their mistakes.

4.title: Episode #6.4
4.plot: Private Tow Edition: In Trenton, Hawk races to his brother-in-law s rescue when a woman flies into a rage. In the Bronx, John and his protégé, Rob meet angry resistance while keeping private lots clear for legitimate customers.

5.title: Episode #6.5
5.plot: Detroit ticketer Ponytail is confronted by an angry man who refuses to see the light. Tow driver John tries to keep illegal parkers honest in the Bronx. Gale force winds threaten to blow Fran off her Providence ticketing beat.

6.title: Episode #6.6
6.plot: In Trenton, Hawk takes his son under his wing when confronted by a crowd of outraged parkers. It's deja vu in Detroit as Eric tickets rowdy repeat offenders. Steve lays down the law in Providence when a driver tries to use an invalid handicap placard.

7.title: Episode #6.7
7.plot: There's hell to pay when Ponytail tickets two guys parked on the sidewalk for a prayer meeting in Detroit. A haircut gone wrong leaves Johnny bald, but brings him good luck while towing in the Bronx. In Providence, Debbie plays cat-and-mouse with a crafty construction worker who continues to park illegally.

8.title: Episode #6.8
8.plot: While towing illegally parked cars in Staten Island, JoJo faces off with a woman accusing him of doing the devil's work. Eric tries to remain courteous while being disrespected in Detroit. In Providence, Maria feels the heat when a citizen refuses to heed her warning.

9.title: Episode #6.9
9.plot: An agitated young man blocks Rob from towing his car in the Bronx. In Providence, Johnny practices tough love but softens for a pair of seniors with a good excuse, while repeat offenders face justice from Judge Caprio in traffic court.

10.title: Episode #6.10
10.plot: Lashelle learns anger management in Detroit when citizens fly into a rage. New York attitude extends to Long Island where Rob tickets bad parkers and even worse drivers, and angry shoppers threaten to call the cops on Hadrick for towing illegally parked cars.

11.title: Episode #6.11
11.plot: In Detroit, Eric amazes with machine-like techniques while ticketing irate parking violators. At Hawk s New Jersey tow lot the gang goes head to head with enraged car owners trying to retrieve their cars. And when an incensed citizen claims he was misled, ticketer Sonja steps in to defend the Detroit she loves.

12.title: Episode #6.12
12.plot: Frustration mounts as Uncle JoJo struggles to get a woman to show her parking permit and avoid his tow truck. Lashelle deals with broken meter mayhem in Detroit and Vinny's tickets upset Long Island residents who think they can park everywhere they're not supposed to.

13.plot: A belligerent man spews venom at Steve as he enforces parking safety in Providence. Lashelle tries to uphold her Detroit parking commandments but ends up ticketing boxing hall of famer Tommy Hearns! And Judge Caprio weighs the excuses of Providence citizens battling their tickets.

14.title: Episode #6.14
14.plot: Mike is caught in the middle of two Staten Island women feuding over a tow. An irate mob confronts Eric for giving rush-hour tickets in front of a popular Detroit market. In North Hempstead, Noreen's motherly patience is tested when she tickets an irate citizen in the fire zone.

15.title: Episode #6.15
15.plot: John flies to the rescue in the Bronx when the irate owner of a towed box truck storms the impound lot. In Detroit angry parkers confront Lashelle even as they confess to know the laws they are breaking, while Ponytail schools agitated citizens on new parking rules during the night shift.

16.title: Episode #6.16
16.plot: In Detroit Ponytail tries to break illegal parkers of their bad habits. Uncle Jojo uses his positive attitude to calm upset Staten Island residents while towing their cars. New parking officer Kristina gets all nature of surprises while ticketing on the night shift in North Hempstead.

17.title: Episode #6.17
17.plot: A Detroit barber and outraged crowd challenge Ponytail over the length of his hair - and the length of a city bus. Little Hawk flies solo towing an abandoned car from a Trenton highway only to have the angry owner storm the lot. Ticketer Betsy tries to keep order as Providence taxi drivers evade the law.

18.title: Episode #6.18
18.plot: In Staten Island Jojo is ambushed by a furious repeat offender who tries to block her car from being towed. Ponytail uses all his powers to stop parking violators in Detroit and Noreen takes no grief from an irate Hempstead store owner parked in the bus zone.

19.title: Episode #6.19
19.plot: While trying to keep Bronx parkers honest, John faces an agitated woman who tries to physically block a tow. In Detroit Lavern stops at nothing to make citizens park properly. Charles has to flash the orange ticket to make illegal parkers in Providence show respect.

20.title: Episode #6.20
20.plot: Ponytail runs into furious Detroit citizens as he tries to catch early bird violators on his morning beat. Bonnie is confronted by argumentative repeat offenders on her Providence ticket beat. Springtime in Detroit brings trouble when Rodney and Sonjia boot at a graduation ceremony.

1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Meet the people Philly loves to hate. Jeff, whose favorite insult is being called "meter maid," squares off with an irate citizen over a broken meter. The booting team of Steve and Sherry encounter a woman who has an extreme emotional attachment to her car. And at the impound lot Maria has a 5-hour face-off with a man trying to get his Mercedes back.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Danielle, who has a reputation for attracting trouble while ticketing, gets into a shouting match during her "rush hour sting." At the impound lot, Rob has a run-in with an angry lady over the paperwork required to get her car back, and Booters Maureen and Jennifer stumble across an unexpected fan.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: On his ticketing beat, Brian has a run-in with a double-parker, while trying to save a stranded hawk in downtown Philly. Veteran tow driver Clarence tests the limits of his compassion while trying to tow a car. In a race against time, Booters Steve and Sherry try to help a man get his tickets paid before the tow truck arrives.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Booters Sherry and Steve deal with threats from an agitated man who wants the boot off now. Fatima looks for a new honey on her ticketing beat, but attracts more bees than boys. At the impound lot, Abdul faces a woman who needs her car so her soldier brother-in-law can be back to base in time for deployment to Iraq.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Paul, known as "Turtle" because he tickets at a slow and steady pace, calls in Supervisor Luz when he can't placate an unhappy citizen. Steve and Sherry have their hands full when a man claims his car got the boot for someone else's tickets. And it's date night at the Lot when charming Rudy faces interrupted romance, and a woman trying to flirt her way out of a fine.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Yolanda has her hands full trying to help the owner of a tricked out pink truck through the red tape to get it released. Tow truck driver John faces a car owner who tries to lock him out, and Marylin makes both friends and enemies as she works her new ticketing beat.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Yolanda faces a screaming couple at the impound lot; Lisa deals with sassy students on the college beat.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Supervisor Brad oversees the madness during Greek Week; Roberta's sunny disposition is put to the test.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: Tow Supervisor Brad oversees the mayhem during Greek Week and the chaos spills over to the Tow Lot, as Larry tries to manage the offenders, without getting disrespected. Meanwhile Roberta's sunny disposition gets put to the test ticketing on the mean streets of Philly.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Yolanda has her hands full trying to help the owner of a tricked-out pink truck through the red tape to get it released. Tow truck driver John faces a car owner who tries to lock him out, and Marylin makes both friends and enemies as she works her new ticketing beat.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: By-the-book ticket writer Danielle teaches Philly drivers tough lessons on the rules of parking. John and Rich scramble to find the missing keys to an impounded car as the owner loses her cool. And it's a lonely day for Garfield when partner Sherry calls in sick, but he finds as much action releasing boots as putting them on.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: An irate mother tries to Retrieve the car her son borrowed without permission, which was towed. Garfield is having phone issues.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: At the Lot, Yolanda tries to help a young man navigate seemingly insurmountable hurdles to get his car back. Booting team Garfield and Sherry experience divine intervention on the job. And 5'1" Carmen faces off with angry construction workers on his ticketing "patrol.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: At the Impound Lot, Yolanda struggles to placate a screaming couple. Booting team Frank and "Cheeks" have a dangerous face off with a man determined to drive off with the boot on. And Lisa takes on smart mouthed students while ticketing on the college beat.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: At the Impound Lot, a rap star faces problems recovering his promotional truck after it was towed. Staunch Philly ticket writer Brian seeks solace from irate citizens in his own "green acre." And a good day's booting turns bad when Garfield gets awful news.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: Chicago tourists push Larry to the breaking point at the impound lot, while Ticket Supervisor Luz tries to toughen up her "nice-guy" rookie Jim, who'd rather be singing on American Idol. Meanwhile Sherry and Garfield go for "quality boots" in busy downtown Philly - with emotional results.

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: At the impound lot, even high comedy cant help two jokesters get their car back. Meanwhile, Marilyn cant find a good man on her Ticketing beat, and Booters Elissa and Rob face serious mischief on the eve of Halloween.

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: Prolific ticketer demonstrates her techniques; a car that crashed into a gas pump gets towed.

1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: At the lot, a woman who's lost the keys to her impounded car, loses her cool -- until Dad steps in. Family man Dave has to tow the car of an irate father of twins. Yolanda won't release a man's impounded car without his mother-in-law. And Tiffany uses her ticket "genie" to find parking violators.

2.title: Episode #2.2
2.plot: At the Lot a couple turns to a higher power to help free their impounded car. Supervisor Ken helps Marilyn take on a ranting sidewalk parker. On their Boot beat, Steve and Sherry face off with an unrepentant scofflaw they once gave a break to.

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: At the impound lot everyone tries to keep the heart rate of an enraged man with a pacemaker from going through the roof. An angry citizen pushes mild-mannered ticket-writer Carmen to the limit. Booter Jen is so gung-ho she'll even work her own street looking to christen a "virgin boot."

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Tracey's style rubs a desperate owner the wrong way.

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: An Israeli tourist battles to get his car released from the lot. A deliveryman unloads his anger on ticket-writer Danielle, and Elissa and Rob give a couple's night out the boot.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: At the lot, Barb squares off with a teen who blames everyone but herself for being towed. On his ticketing beat, Shawn has a run in with a couple parked on the sidewalk. And while booting the mailman, Jen and Mike face off with an angry mob.

9.title: Episode #2.9
9.plot: As the PPA deals with the tense aftermath of a fatal cop shooting, tow driver Frank is called to the scene of a volatile live stop. Glamorous ticket-writer Marlene encounters a chronic parking violator who ends up at the lot in search of her impounded car.

10.title: Episode #2.10
10.plot: At the lot a woman struggles to get back the car that was towed while she was in labor. Temperature and tempers reach boiling point for Steve and Sherry on the boot shift. Ticket Supervisor Luz must face an angry man who was ticketed at a broken meter.

11.title: Episode #2.11
11.plot: The clock is ticking as late night partiers try to get their car before the lot closes. Booters Steve and Sherry have to brave a tempest and Tim gets an earful from the wild crowds while ticketing on South Street.

12.title: Episode #2.12
12.plot: A new resident struggles to get his car after being towed on his first day in Philly. Shawn can't keep up with the tickets in front of a famous hoagie shop, and Neema deals with being the only female tow driver on the squad.

13.title: Episode #2.13
13.plot: Two guys try to get their car back before they miss their flight to Atlanta. Hunter Mike gives tickets.

14.title: Episode #2.14
14.plot: At the lot it's a race against time for a man trying to get his car off the auction block. Sherry takes on the challenge of booting while Steve watches her back, and ticket writer Marlene has a showdown with angry citizens and her unruly hair.

15.title: Episode #2.15
15.plot: Marylin takes it to heart when a man she tickets flies into a rage. The hurdles may be too high for a couple struggling to retrieve the impounded car they adore. Cursed by Sherry, Steve loses his Mojo and nothing goes right on their boot beat.

16.title: Episode #2.16
16.plot: The lot gets hot when three brothers team up to retrieve their impounded car. Garfield and Sherry encounter their largest booting target ever, while Brian faces the flames of hell on his ticketing beat.

29.title: Episode #2.29
29.plot: At the lot, a woman's anger stands in the way of getting her car back, while Lisa has to contend with a stalker on her ticketing beat. A man seeks compensation for his wrongly impounded car, and Neema, the Queen of Towing, is surprised by a wild stolen car story.

1.title: Episode #3.1
1.plot: Meet the people the Motor City loves to hate. DeAndre, nicknamed "Ponytail" for his long lock of hair, faces off with an irate citizen over parking on city property. Michele and Sonjia, the all-female "Super Boot Crew", boot a woman who's dead husband may have racked up tickets on her car. And rookie Sonja doles out compassion along with tickets.

2.title: Episode #3.2
2.plot: Garfield and Sherry need police backup when a furious man tries to remove a boot.

3.title: Episode #3.3
3.plot: Sparks fly as Mike stumbles onto a parking fiasco at a Philly gala event. Rodney and Michele catch red-handed a Detroiter in the act of removing a boot. And brotherly love is put to the test when two Jersey boys try to rescue their hoopdie from the Philly impound lot.

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: Philadelphia ticket writer Jeff returns to the lot, this time as a newly promoted supervisor. When tempers flare on South Street on Saturday night, he runs to the rescue of his new squad that includes Denise, a rookie learning the ropes and Gina, a magnate for male attention.

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: A hit and run throws Detroit booters Courtney and Sonjia off their beat. At the Philly impound lot, a son struggles to get his car back after his father was caught speeding without a license. And it's all fireworks in Detroit when Ponytail tries to enforce a special parking ordnance for the Fourth of July.

6.title: Episode #3.6
6.plot: After losing 70lbs, Detroit ticketer Robert is extra confident when challenged by an outraged man who parked commercial equipment on the street. In Philly, ticketer Marlene's years of experience give her the upper hand when insulted by a group of young men, and at the lot, Yolanda's service with a smile turns into a big headache for a fast food manager struggling to retrieve his impounded car.

7.title: Episode #3.7
7.plot: In Philly, Garfield tests his Irish luck trying to boot two cars on the same block, until one citizen gets physical. Can Detroit ticketer Robert, know as "Mr. Perfection" for lack of voided tickets, keep his record when challenged by irate citizens? A 70 year-old man's patience is tested as he tries to get his car out of the Philly impound lot.

8.title: Episode #3.8
8.plot: Police are called in when Jen and Mike face off with an angry man who resorts to extreme measures--and a garden tool--to try to get them to remove the boot. At the lot, a brother and sister from out of town struggle to find their impounded car that is lost in the system.

9.title: Episode #3.9
9.plot: As the PPA deals with the tense aftermath of a fatal cop shooting, tow driver Frank is called to the scene of a volatile live stop. Glamorous ticket-writer Marlene encounters a chronic parking violator who ends up at the lot in search of her impounded car.

10.title: Episode #3.10
10.plot: In Detroit the tough guys call in sick so the ladies make the rounds booting cars with the occasional help from the police. The queen of handicapped parking spaces makes her rounds. And more documentation trouble at the impound lot.

11.title: Episode #3.11
11.plot: Welcome to Snow-adelphia! A blizzard drops ten inches of snow, adding aggravation for people struggling to free their cars from the impound lot. Meanwhile, snow, ice, and freezing temperatures make big trouble for booters Garfield and Sherry.

12.title: Episode #3.12
12.plot: In Detroit, Rodney and Sonjia must watch each other's backs when a foul-mouthed man challenges the boot on his car. Supervisor Luz fends off crafty ticket dodgers in Philly, until a self-appointed neighborhood watchman tries to stop her from ticketing his neighbor's car. Philly Ticketer Shawn uses "the force" to find good tickets--but gets caught off guard when he writes one in error.

13.title: Episode #3.13
13.plot: In Detroit, Rodney and Sonjia must watch each other's backs when a foul-mouthed man challenges the boot on his car. Supervisor Luz fends off crafty ticket dodgers in Philly, until a self-appointed neighborhood watchman tries to stop her from ticketing his neighbor's car. Philly Ticketer Shawn uses "the force" to find good tickets--but gets caught off guard when he writes one in error.

1.title: Episode #4.1
1.plot: In Philly, a man struggling to retrieve his impounded car takes a back seat when his wife flies into a rage. Sweet-natured ticket-writer Lachelle is shouted down by a Detroit woman who claims she has time on her meter. And in Philly, Sherry celebrates her birthday booting with Garfield, but faces a woman who won't stop crying.

2.title: Episode #4.2
2.plot: In Philly, an infuriated woman calls the cops on rookie Richie for writing tickets! And in Detroit, Rodney and Sonjia lock horns with an angry man who uses his kids to try and stop his booted car being towed, while ticketer Sonja has it out with repeat offenders when patrolling handicap spaces.

3.title: Episode #4.3
3.plot: Night booting in Philly gets out of hand when Frank and Rob are ambushed by an irate heavy-hitter. Motor city ticket-writer Ponytail is a talented "car whisperer," but the volume gets cranked up when he faces a threatening citizen. And outrage rules the lot, as a woman takes on the city and the PPA to fight a $1000 ticket.

4.title: Episode #4.4
4.plot: Night booting in Philly gets out of hand when Frank and Rob are ambushed by an irate heavy-hitter. Motor city ticket-writer Ponytail is a talented "car whisperer," but the volume gets cranked up when he faces a threatening citizen. And outrage rules the lot, as a woman takes on the city and the PPA to fight a $1000 ticket.

5.title: Episode #4.5
5.plot: In Philly, rookie ticket-writer Ritchie tries to play by the rules with an irate citizen, Yolanda helps a frustrated out of town couple to try to recover their car when they hit a wall. And on the night shift tow driver Dave works busy South Street but has to face off with some uncooperative partiers!

6.title: Episode #4.6
6.plot: In Detroit Michele and Courtney need police back up when a furious woman literally pushes them to the limit. Philly Ticketer Shawn calls supervisor Jeff for help in a broken meter stand-off, and at the lot, an irate father and son learn they can't escape their unpaid tickets.

7.title: Episode #4.7
7.plot: Kim runs into verbal abuse from angry Detroit citizens who think the city is to blame for their tickets. In Philly, a young man tries to alter his expired registration to free his impounded car, and Garfield tries to convince Sherry that his lucky pants will help them boot.

8.title: Episode #4.8
8.plot: In Detroit an enraged mother and daughter call on the wrath of God to damn Sonjia and Courtney for booting their car. In Philly, Denise gets an earful from a man furious that he was ticketed while helping his handicapped son, and a virgin to the impound lot tries to free her car.

9.title: Episode #4.9
9.plot: In Detroit, boot releaser Sonjia must calm irate citizens after Rodney and Courtney boot their cars. And in Philly, a frustrated man at the impound lot asks "Dude, where's my car?" as Marylin encounters the "frenemy" while ticketing in a rowdy neighborhood.

10.title: Episode #4.10
10.plot: Philly ticketer Shawn faces off with pizza shop employees who think they're above the law. Detroit booters Rodney and Courtney clash with a man who blames the city for his ticket troubles. An exotic dancer calls on two ex-lovers to free a car from the Philly impound lot.

11.title: Episode #4.11
11.plot: In Detroit, Louann tickets vehicles for blocking an alley. At the Philly impound lot, a man faces challenges to get his car released. Sherry and Garfield deal with unique South Philly residents.

12.title: Episode #4.12
12.plot: In Detroit a furious citizen challenges LouAnn over a ticket for blocking an alley. A man struggling to free his car from the Philly impound faces seemingly endless setbacks, and on their booting beat Garfield and Sherry run into a South Philly character right out of Goodfellas.

13.title: Episode #4.13
13.plot: In Detroit, cars in front of a mosque are ticketed. A woman is booted after a baseball game, because of tickets to her dead husband. In, Philadelphia Brian is having a bad day.

14.title: Episode #4.14
14.plot: Marylin faces an enraged stalker on her Philly ticket beat. In Detroit, a woman booted on a job interview hurls insults at Rodney and Sonjia. Two ex's are reunited at the Philly impound lot after a car crash.

15.title: Episode #4.15
15.plot: In Philly, Jeff tickets foulmouthed truck drivers unloading freight and insults in a no stopping zone. Booter Sherry dares Garfield to dye his hair to match their most booted car color that day. And a man tries to help his girlfriend spring the car he got towed on her birthday.

16.title: Episode #4.16
16.plot: Garfield and Sherry go on the chase when a Philly citizen speeds off with the boot on. All bets are off when Ponytail confronts two screaming women who gamble with illegal parking in Detroit. In Philly, a DJ's head spins when the gets the runaround at the impound lot.

17.title: Episode #4.17
17.plot: In Philly, a furious mother and son cause a fracas when they cut to the front of the line at the lot. And Richie faces his nightmare beat when his "Jersey Shore" hairdo is threatened by the rain. Detroit ticketer Kim meets opposition as she tries to clear the road for street cleaners.

18.title: Episode #4.18
18.plot: In Detroit, Rodney and Sonjia are challenged by an irate man claiming he's a sovereign. In Philly, it's Richie against the Old City crowds on a rowdy Friday night, and everyone at the lot tries to help an elderly woman retrieve the car her grandson caused to be towed only to discover an unpleasant surprise in the front seat.

19.title: Episode #4.19
19.plot: Angry Philly citizens shake Garfield out of his post vacation idle. In Detroit an irate woman stalks Norman as he tries to ticket for street cleaning violations. The past comes back to haunt two brothers trying to retrieve their car from the Philly impound lot.

20.title: Episode #4.20
20.plot: This one-hour special counts down the top 10 outrageous encounters between illegal parkers and the Philadelphia Parking Authority from the past four seasons.

22.title: Episode #4.22
22.plot: In Philly, two women scramble to retrieve the car a valet got towed during their night of partying, and Garfield and Sherry boot some unhappy citizens as they hunt scofflaws. In Detroit, ticket writer Robert tries to teach old dogs new tricks.

23.title: Episode #4.23
23.plot: An angry man can't retrieve the rental car that was towed when he took his wife to the hospital. Ticketer Shawn is confronted by angry citizens and Philly icon Marlene meets her match on her ticketing beat.

24.title: Episode #4.24
24.plot: Ponytail has the holiday spirit in Detroit . In Philly, a woman is trying to get her car back that her son had stolen from the impound yard. Brian gets an unwanted gift after a shift of giving tickets.

25.title: Episode #4.25
25.plot: Clerical errors cause a car to be towed in Philadelphia. Booting in Detroit before Christmas. Back in Philly, Gina tickets on South Street.

26.title: Episode #4.26
26.plot: In Philadelphia, Shawn faces off with parking violators as he tries to keep the streets safe for kids, while relationships get strained over impounded cars at the lot, and tow driver John deals with outraged bystanders.

1.title: Episode #5.1
1.plot: Marylin faces an enraged stalker on her Philly ticket beat. In Detroit, a woman booted on a job interview hurls insults at Rodney and Sonjia. Two ex's are reunited at the Philly impound lot after a car crash.

2.title: Episode #5.2
2.plot: Booting on a Saturday brings Michele and Courtney face to face with an angry Detroit restaurant owner. In Providence, Charles is called every name in the book except his real one as he tries to keep the bus lane clear. When she has to work a ticket beat, Detroit booter Sonjia gets more abuse than she's used to.

3.title: Episode #5.3
3.plot: In Detroit, Rodney & Sonjia boot a man who insists he's already paid all his tickets. "Johnny Tickets" meets angry opposition as he lives up to his nickname in Providence. Sonja's confronted by an angry mob at a Detroit bar while ticketing.

4.title: Episode #5.4
4.plot: Detroit Booters Courtney and Sonjia run afoul of a football player when he uses his heft to block his mama's car from being towed. Ticketer Debbie battles noise and an irate man in downtown Providence. In Detroit, Ponytail confronts lots of mischief on his ticket beat.

5.plot: In Detroit, Lashelle tries to counsel sisters furious over a corner violation. Two Providence men confront Johnny after they are ticketed for paying the wrong meter. Ponytail is all business while challenged by angry citizens in Detroit.

6.plot: A furious man challenges booters Rodney and Michele as they try to uphold the law. Providence citizens berate Charles even when the violations are obvious. The insults get personal when Sonjia tickets an irate violator in Detroit.

7.plot: In Detroit, a day releasing Michele and Courtney's boots turns wild for Rodney when a man tries to drive off in the middle of a tow. Then, Kim squares off with a citizen who removes a handicap parking sign the city installed just for him!

8.plot: In Detroit, an unrelenting car dealer challenges Lashelle over parking on the sidewalk. Ticketer Mary uses her experience raising seven kids to discipline unruly citizens in Providence, and things heat up in Detroit as Eric tries to keep fire hydrants clear for firefighters battling a blaze.

9.plot: Ponytail brings down a Detroit ticket storm until he meets his very irate match. Rodney & Sonjia are involved in a high-speed booting chase. And in Providence, Evelyn faces off with an angry violator as she patrols the Italian neighborhood.

10.plot: Ponytail has a run-in with a gang of Beauty School students who threaten to cut his tail. In Providence, Bonnie is confronted by an irate man who claims his violation is void because of a missing sign. When Rodney boots a car in a busy area of Detroit, Sonjia is forced to direct traffic.

11.plot: In Detroit, Eric gets disrespected by am angry man ticketed next to his own home. Patty tries to shame Providence parkers into playing by the rules. Louann is challenged by repeat offenders who think they shouldn't get tickets for breaking the law!

12.title: Episode #5.12
12.plot: In Detroit, nosy neighbors give Eric more grief than the actual violators, and Sonjia & Courtney are confronted by a distraught man who's been booted while using an illegal license plate. Meanwhile, former crossing-guard Kathy has a bone to pick when ticketing crosswalk parkers in Providence.

13.title: Episode #5.13
13.plot: Lashelle faces angry parkers caught in Detroit's ticket Bermuda triangle. Steve is confronted by an irate Providence woman who refuses to believe the law. In Detroit, Darryl Lee tries but fails to keep his last day of work peaceful.

15.title: Episode #5.15
15.plot: In Detroit, Rodney and Sonjia boot a man who insists he's already paid all his tickets. "Johnny Tickets" meets angry opposition as he lives up to his nickname in Providence. Sonia is confronted by an angry mob at a Detroit bar while ticketing.

16.title: Episode #5.16
16.plot: Detroit Booters Courtney and Sonjia run afoul of a football player when he uses his heft to block his mama's car from being towed. Ticketer Debbie battles noise and an irate man in downtown Providence. In Detroit, Ponytail confronts lots of mischief on his ticket beat.
